text.section:
The Department shall certify any individual who:
Meets the requirements of this subtitle;
Meets the Department's educational requirements, including a program on the proper application of nutrients;
Passes a Department approved examination; and
Is employed by a person licensed under this subtitle; or
Holds a license as required by this subtitle.

The Department shall renew the certificate or license of any applicant for a 3-year term if the applicant:
Submits a renewal application on the form that the Department requires;
Pays to the Department the applicable fee stated in § 8-806 of this subtitle;
Complies with applicable continuing education requirements;
Complies with applicable record keeping and reporting requirements; and
Otherwise is entitled to be certified or licensed.

section.section:
The certificate is valid provided the person operating the farm:
Has paid the one-time fee provided in § 8-806 of this subtitle;
Has passed an examination as determined by the Department;
Complies with applicable continuing education requirements;
Complies with applicable record keeping and reporting requirements; and
Otherwise is entitled to be certified.
